Roles and Headers

Assign app to Everyone role

To view the app in runtime, you must assign the app to a role. In this step, youll assign the Create Sales Order AC096819U21 build app to the Everyone role. This is a default role - content assigned to the Everyone role is visible to all users.

  1. Open the Content Manager from the side panel.

  2. Click the Everyone role to open the role editor.

  3. Click Edit.

  4. Click the search box in the Assignments panel on the right. Any available apps are shown in the list below.

  5. Next to the Create Sales Order AC096819U21 build app, click the + icon (use the search box to locate your App if needed). Youll see that the icon changes.

NOTE: If you have not created any app as part of Build Apps TA, you can add Generic build app as shown below.

  1. Click Save.

To see the app in the Applications page, you can assign it to a new or existing group. This is an optional step and is not required for this workshop.

Add a header for your most frequently used apps

Before you add the Create Sales Order AC096819U21 build app to your workspace, first add a header for a section where you will add most frequently used apps.

  1. Open your workspace Sales Management AC096819U21.

  2. Click the pencil icon to open the Page Designer.

  3. Scroll down to the section just before the Feed and click + to add another section.

  4. Click Add Widget to open the widget gallery.

  5. Select the Text widget and design it as follows:

    Text Type in the following: Most Popular Apps
    Font Select the text and change to Arial 14pt.
    Color With the text still selected, choose the color black from the chart.

  6. To increase the spacing between this section and the section above, hover to expose the settings on the right, and click the cog icon to edit the spacing.

  7. Under Padding Top add the value 30 pixels and click Save.

Now youre going to add your app under this header.
